Recipients with their own "electronic goods ticket" Setouchi City added with hometown tax: Sanyo Newspaper Digital | San Diego
"E-City Gift."
it's settled by contacting a dedicated device.
Setouchi City announced on the 27th that it will add its own electronic goods ticket "e-machi Gift" to the return goods of hometown tax.
It is available at member stores in the city from November.
It was the first municipality in the prefecture.
If you pay Furusato tax and choose an electronic goods ticket as a reward item, 30% of the donation amount will be sent to the designated smartphone.
When purchasing a product, it shows the screen of the product ticket, and the shop side pays by contacting a stamp-type dedicated device.
They cannot be sold or sold.
Recipients usually require a certain amount of time from application to arrival, but electronic goods tickets can be received instantly.
Tourists can use it easily.
In addition to the five Hometown Tax Portals, there are also two special sites in the city.
The company currently has 13 member stores, with a target of 100 by the end of this fiscal year.
In June, the Ministry of Internal Affairs and Communications (MIC) established a new system to regulate local products in order to prevent excessive competition among municipalities, with the amount of return gifts raised to 30% or less of the donation amount.
The city has stated that "the city plans to set up merchants who handle local products as members, and within the guidelines."
In fiscal 2018, Setouchi City's hometown tax amount was approximately 430 million yen.
