Self-improvement of safety measures at Famaspo 35% of municipalities implemented, free of charge for child care | Shizuoka Shimbun at Ess
Bereaved families of child-care accidents (right) holding a press conference on the results of the "Family Support Center Project" = On the afternoon of the 27th, Osaka Prefecture Agency
According to a private survey on the 27th, 35% of municipal towns and villages in Ichi Ward have independently strengthened safety measures for "Family Support Center Project" (Famispo), which connects parents who want to temporarily leave their children and support members who are in private homes.
Prior to the provision of free child education and childcare in October, the family members of the childcare accident complained that the country should make strict standards.
The "Network to Eliminate Serious Accidents in Childcare" created by parents and experts who lost their children in an accident during childcare was investigated by 921 municipalities.
274 municipalities responded.
The government's guidelines only require aid members to take emergency life training courses.
