[Saga Torrential Rainfall and Support Wheel] Specialty Noodles "Taromen" Perform at evacuation centers Management Co-op, Revitalizing Victims|Saga Shimbun News|Saga Shimbun
Children who enjoy the soul food "Taromen" in Omachi on their way home from the bath = Misato, Omachi Town General Welfare Center
"Omachi Taromen Steering Council" (Representative of Kensuke Suzuyama) made at a restaurant serving "Taromen," a specialty noodle of Omachi-cho, performed "Taromen" at Misato, Machi General Welfare Center, which is a shelter for people affected by heavy rain on the night of the 25th.
The soul food that was loved since the Kishima coal mine was there cheered the people affected.
"The only thing we can do is make noodles and eat them."
Four restaurants on the taromen menu cooperated to make 90 meals, and brought rice balls to shelter.
Udon noodles of fine noodles were put in ginger-flavored beef bone soup, and ingredients such as pork head meat, shrimp, and vegetables were abundant.
In addition to those who stayed at evacuation centers, they also provided "taste of Omachi" to those who came to the bath provided by the SDF.
A man (66) says, "I've been a fan since I was young, but I ate it for the first time in a year," and a 20-year-old and 22-year-old siblings who moved about a year ago and said, "I ate it for the first time, it's delicious, I want to go to the store this time."
Vice President Kenichiro Fujise, who finished cooking, also ran up and said, "We will cooperate if we can, so that we can return to our daily life as soon as possible."
1 year after the earthquake in the eastern part of Iburi Province Water supply even when power outages proceed with the installation of "water sprinkling plugs" directly connected to water pipes Hakodate Mansion: Hokkaido Shimbun
In response to the total blackout (blackout) caused by the Iburi Eastern Earthquake in September last year, measures are being taken at condominiums in Hakodate City, where water breaks out.
According to the Water and Sewer Department of the City Bureau of Enterprises, seven condominiums in one year after the earthquake installed "watering plugs" that could produce water even if power outages occurred.
There are about 400 condominiums and private housing units in the city that supply water with a "water tank type" that can be cut off during power outage, and the department calls for consideration of countermeasures.
The water supply system for houses is broadly divided into two types: the "passenger tank type" for water once placed in a receiving tank located underground or on the roof, and the "directly connected type" for watering directly from the city's water distribution pipe to each door.
Even if the water pipe is not damaged, electric pumps that pump water from the water tank to each door will not be able to run due to power failure, and each door will be cut off.
Training (Aomori Broadcasting Corporation) - Yahoo!
A training session was held in Shingo Village to search for and rescue the victims before the autumn mushroom harvest season.
The training at Hirakozawa Forest Park in Shingo Village was attended by 60 people from the police, firefighting, and hunting party.
At the opening ceremony, Chief Tsukeda of the Goto Police Department called for close cooperation and training.
★ Takahashi Regional Manager's declaration "We will start mountain training rescue training from this."
The training was conducted on the assumption that a man who went out to see the mushroom harvest would not return home even at night.
Participants are divided into three groups and search through the mountains with the name of a missing man.
In Shingo Village, a 70-year-old man who entered the mountain in June to pick up wild vegetables disappeared and was rescued with injuries the next day.
During the training, I found a man who had been injured and checked the cooperation between search and rescue on a stretcher to go down the mountain.
