"Snake" image overlaps with beautiful girls of Kazuo Baizu's work (Magmics) - Yahoo!News
Is the mysterious beauty and the expression of the shadow in common?
Since the 1950s, many works have been sent out to the world, and "Baizu Kazuo Bijo Collection" (Genkosha) was released in August 2019.
When I look at it with my hands, I notice the correlation between "beauty" and "fear" of Kazuo Baizu's work again.
[Image ] Is it attractive because there is a shadow?
Five beautiful girls of Kazuo Bai painting
In the preface of the "Beautiful Girl Collection," there was a statement that "fear, ugliness, shocking scenes and developments of the story stand out only when there is the beauty of these women who are at the opposite end."
There is a keyword "snake" in what appears many in Baizu Kazuo's work, but snakes are perceived as "spicy creatures" by the viewer, and there are people who feel "beautiful."
Some people like reptiles in the world, and others don't like them.
In this way, depending on the sensibilities of the viewer, "beauty" and "ugly evil" may be "snakes" of the living things in the front and back.
Also, this creature has been worshiped as a spiritual creature since ancient times, and it is said that the house where "white snake" lived is good luck.
There are "Hebi Girl" and "Later Girl" in the 1965 series "Mama ga Kowai!."
In most cases, a beautiful woman with a shadow is the market price.
If you put it in an imaginative way, can you say it is a "cool beauty" type ... ... I feel that it is the common point of beauty girls appearing in Baizu works.
Among them, "Orochi," the main character of "Orochi," which was serialized in "Weekly Shonen Sunday" since 1969, is a beautiful girl character that can be said to be the representative of Baizu works, but in order to keep eternal life and eternal youth, deep sleep every 100 years, and the part with strange power somehow reminiscent of "snake."
