Bic Camera Okayama Ekimae store where sales of large home appliances are strong before the tax increase.
On the 28th, the last weekend before the consumption tax hike, from 8% to 10%, family members who had been buying and selling goods at home appliance stores and supermarkets in Okayama Prefecture visited one after another.
There is also a home center that develops a special shop to buy a summary, and a suit store that sells winter clothing in front of it, and each store is putting effort into selling.
Bic Camera Okayama Station Branch (Kita Ward, Okayama City, Ekimae-cho) offers a limited-time sale until 30 days.
A man from a company in the city (37) who came to the store looking for a refrigerator said, "Although it is 2%, the difference can not be seen if it is expensive."
According to the store, large-scale home appliances such as TVs, washing machines, and refrigerators increased in September, and sales were about double that of the previous year.
"The rush-in demand is beyond imagination, and in the second half, customers who seek expensive goods stand out."
The sale, which is said to be a large-scale settlement just before the tax increase, is carried out by Haruyama Shoji Co., Ltd., a suit sales company.
Coats have been sold since early September, a month earlier than usual, and sales this month are expected to increase by 10% compared to the previous year.
A company employee (19) who visited Kurashiki store (Shiraraku-cho, Kurashiki City) to buy a suit for an adult ceremony = Asaguchi City = "The ceremony is still ahead, but I want to buy it before tax increase."
