Minister of Health, Labour and Welfare Meets with the Family of Leprosy Three Provincial Consultations to Eliminate Discrimination | Shizuoka Shimbun at Ess
Katsunobu Kato, Minister of Health, Labour and Welfare, announced at a press conference after the Cabinet meeting on October 27 that he would meet with the families of former leprosy patients on October 2.
He also announced that the Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare, Ministry of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology, and Ministry of Justice would hold consultations on the same day to resolve discrimination and prejudice against former patients and their families.
Mr. Kato said, "I would like to listen carefully to the voices of the family members and make every effort to solve the problem."
In June, the Kumamoto District Court ordered 541 plaintiffs to pay a total of 376 million yen.
Prime Minister Abe Shinzō announced his appeal and the decision was finalized.
The government also worked on compensation measures and human rights awareness.
