The possibility of hybridization (response) - Yahoo!News
Jaguar's first crossover SUV , "F-PACE" The camera captured the new improved prototype for the first time in Southern Europe.
F-PACE originated from the 4-seater concept SUV C-X17, which was first released in 2013.
The five-seater version was released in 2014 and officially debuted at the Frankfurt Motor Show in 2015.
The first model was released in 2016 and this is the first facelift.
The prototype captured is covered with thick camouflage, but part of the new design can be seen.
The headlights are more compact and thin, and the side air intake is also modified to a sporty oval.
The grill is completely disguised, but it will definitely be redesigned.
In the rear end, a portion of the redesigned taillight can be seen, equipped with a narrow reverse light at the top.
It seems that there is a possibility that the design that moves greatly to the side like the current model is compactly modified.
Inside the cabin, the company's touch screen infotainment system is expected to be installed, and new digital clusters, HVAC control screens, steering wheels, and gear selectors will be refreshed.
The powertrain is expected to include a 2.0-liter inline four-cylinder turbodiesel and a hybrid 3.0-liter inline six-cylinder indium.
The world premiere will be in 2020.
